    "body": "You can use `forge run` for that, e.g. `forge run path/to/Contract.sol --sig \"someFunc(uint256,uint256)\" 1 2` would run `someFunc(uint256,uint256)` in `path/to/Contract.sol` with parameters 1 and 2.\r\n\r\nAlternatively, you can use `--sig 0xbeef` where `0xbeef` is the entire calldata\r\n\r\n`forge run` also supports forking :)",
